The reason I said str is better is simply because I dont get hit that often.  Perhaps this is a result of not inflicting enough damage to gain aggro(currently using trak tooth and cier'dal(?) spine razor.) <br>
Actually, it occurs to me; the more str you have the greater damage you do, the more damage you do the more aggro you get, the more aggro you get the more you get hit, and in turn the more sta you need to stay alive.(Just an off-hand observation)<br>
Anyway... exactly what is the benefit of sta?  It looks to me like more sta = more hp, but is there anything else that it contributes to? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udeclspec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>  declspec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 1:42:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12871.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> the more damage thing is barely there though.<br>
